                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.6363/145: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hammond</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-12-08T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 8, 1928—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>68. Your 100, December 6, 10 a.m. Your failure to inform the Department of the
                    French Ambassador’s action on November 30 at Madrid and also to consult the
                    Department before sending your note dated December 4 to the Spanish Government
                    is surprising.</p>
                <p>The Department and oil companies are in consultation. The situation created by
                    your note will be dealt with in further instructions early next week.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
